Generalizing the Code Chunk
How can this be generalized to other languages?


```{r, echo=FALSE}
rnorm(3)
```


Executable code flagged by { }

The Perks of the Hashpipe #|


Line breaks prevent chunk options that go on {r, and=on, and=on, and=on, and=on, and=on, and=on}




Chunk options are now pan-language with &lt;commentchar&gt;|.



```{python}
#| echo: false
```

```{mermaid}
%%| echo: false
```





No more yelling! (eval=FALSE)

